e,"excerpt":"Umar ibn al-Khattab reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDo not exaggerate my status\u00a0as the Christians have done with the son of Mary. Verily, I am only a servant, so refer to me as the servant of Allah and His Messenger.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6682,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/20\/dhikr-often-or-hard-heart\/","url_meta":{"origin":34254,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Dhikr: Mention Allah often, or heart will harden","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 20, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDo not speak too much without mentioning Allah. Verily, talking too much without remembering Allah hardens the heart. The furthest of people from Allah is one with a hard heart.\" Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2411 Grade: Hasan\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":843,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/06\/08\/cruel-not-enter-paradise\/","url_meta":{"origin":34254,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Cruelty: Harsh, mean people do not enter Paradise","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 8, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Harithah ibn Wahb reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNeither the haughty, nor the cruel,